# Images and game assets

- When implementing UI, care mode, battle, or any feature that needs sprites, icons, or pixel art, **use image generation directly** and save under `public/pets/` or the right `public/` subfolder. **Do not ask permission for every asset** unless the user has opted out.
- Keep designs **original**; do not copy commercial IP (e.g. Digimon, Pokemon) or official art.
- Prefer **true alpha PNG**. If generating with AI, ask for **flat magenta `#FF00FF` studio** (no black letterbox) then run **`npm run strip-magenta`** (`scripts/strip-magenta-bg.mjs`) before **`npm run optimize:pets`**. If the model still bakes a **gray / magenta checkerboard or white slab**, run **`npm run strip-pet-flood`** (`scripts/strip-edge-flood-bg.mjs`) on that PNG (green／黃核心膨脹＋邊緣淹沒＋淺白／紫邊清理)；若還有**淺灰暈邊**，再試 **`npm run strip-pet-matte`**。 **Never** bake in checkerboard / gray-white grid “transparency preview” pixels. In prompts forbid: checkerboard, transparency grid, placeholder grid.
- **Recurring issue — fake transparency:** AI sprites often ship with a **solid light-gray or off-white rectangle** behind the subject (not real alpha). This shows up against the game panel (`--screen`, care bezel, etc.). **Always** treat “transparent background” in the prompt as unreliable: after export, check the PNG on a **non-white** background or in the running UI; if a matte appears, fix the asset (CSS alone usually cannot remove baked-in pixels).
  - **Fix patterns:** (1) magenta key + chroma strip (above); (2) for uniform studio mats, a small **Node + sharp** pass — e.g. egg cleanup `scripts/strip-egg-gray.mjs` (border color sample + light neutral matte removal); run **`npm run strip-egg-bg`** after replacing egg PNGs; (3) for **idle / pose sprites** (cat, chicken, pet-*) use **`scripts/strip-creature-matte.mjs`** → **`npm run strip-pet-matte`** (corner matte estimate + neutral / cool-gray pass); (4) re-prompt stricter (“alpha only, no gray, no white backdrop”) and post-process again if needed.
- Idle art is **per growth stage**: `public/pets/pet-idle-s0.png` … `pet-idle-s4.png` (see `idleSpriteForSpeciesStage` in `src/pet.ts`). Care action filenames per species: **`carePoseFile`** in `src/pet.ts`, used from `src/main.ts`.
- After adding or replacing pet PNGs under `public/pets/`, run **`npm run optimize:pets`** (`scripts/optimize-pet-pngs.mjs`: max edge 256px, nearest resize, zlib level 9) and commit the optimized output so first load stays small.
- After adding files, if blobs are still very large (~500KB+ per sprite), suggest further compression (e.g. Squoosh) or consider WebP with a small loader change.
